gomodel:SYNGO_2083  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Single-label experiments also show anti-α5 immunogold particles that are associated with synapses (arrows, Fig. 4 I-K), frequently having symmetric, or Gray's type 2, morphology (Fig. 4 I and J).\"\n\nFig,5: \"Double-labeling experiments with the postsynaptic GABAergic markers β2/3 or γ2 GABAAR subunits or gephyrin (Fig. 5 F-Q), showed that the α5 immunoreactivity (arrows, Fig. 5 F-N), was associated with synaptic membranes at GABAergic synapses.\". Experimental description: \"Briefly, 35-70 day old Sprague Dawley rats were anesthetized as described above and perfused with 800 ...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
